  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 2, 23, 15, 52, 58.762248}", 
    "history" -> {"14.3", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickScramblingSimulate[in, {a, b}, spec, ..., dep] simulates quantum \
information scrambling circuits of depth 0, 1, 2, ..., dep and returns the \
list of the absolute values of out-of-time-order correlator (OTOC) between \
two local unitary operators a and b. For the remaining arguments spec, ..., \
see RandomWickCircuit. WickScramblingSimulate[..., {dep, ds}] simulates \
circuits of depth 0, ds, 2 ds, ..., dep in the forward-time evolution part. \
WickScramblingSimulate[in, {i, j}, spec, ...] assumes a := exp[\\[Pi]/2 ( \
f_i^\\[Dagger] f i + 1 - f_i + 1^\\[Dagger] fi)] and b := 1 - 2 \
f_j^\\[Dagger] fj, where fk is the k^th fermion mode. \
WickScramblingSimulate[in, i, spec, ...] is equivalent to \
WickScramblingSimulate[in, {i, 1}, spec, ...].", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "WickScramblingSimulate", "titlemodifier" -> 
    "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "WickScramblingSimulate", 
    "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/WickScramblingSimulate"}},
